void
EmitIR::operator()(ReturnStmt* obj)
{
  auto& irb = *mCurIrb;
  if (!obj->expr) {
    irb.CreateRetVoid();
  } else {
    auto retVal = self(obj->expr);
    irb.CreateRet(retVal);
  }
  auto exitBb = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(mCtx, "return_exit", mCurFunc);
  irb.SetInsertPoint(exitBb);
}

//==============================================================================
// 声明
//==============================================================================

void
EmitIR::operator()(Decl* obj)
{
  if (auto p = obj->dcst<VarDecl>())
    return self(p);

  if (auto p = obj->dcst<FunctionDecl>())
    return self(p);

  ABORT();
}

void
EmitIR::operator()(VarDecl* obj)
{
  // 全局变量
  if (mCurFunc == nullptr) {
    auto ty = self(obj->type);
    llvm::Constant* initVal;
    if (obj->init)
      initVal = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(self(obj->init));
    else
      initVal = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ty);
    auto gv = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
      mMod, ty, obj->type->qual.const_,
      llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage, initVal, obj->name);
    obj->any = gv;
    return;
  }

  // 局部变量
  auto ty = self(obj->type);
  auto alloca = getOrCreateAlloca(ty, obj->name);
  obj->any = alloca;
  if (obj->init) {
    auto initVal = self(obj->init);
    mCurIrb->CreateStore(initVal, alloca);
  }
}

void
EmitIR::operator()(FunctionDecl* obj)
{
  auto fty = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::FunctionType>(self(obj->type));
  auto func = llvm::Function::Create(
    fty, llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage, obj->name, mMod);

  obj->any = func;

  if (obj->body == nullptr)
    return;

  mSymtbl.clear();

  auto entryBb = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(mCtx, "entry", func);
  mCurIrb->SetInsertPoint(entryBb);
  auto& entryIrb = *mCurIrb;

  // 处理函数参数
  for (auto&& arg : func->args()) {
    auto paramDecl = obj->params[arg.getArgNo()];
    auto alloca = entryIrb.CreateAlloca(arg.getType(), nullptr, paramDecl->name);
    entryIrb.CreateStore(&arg, alloca);
    paramDecl->any = alloca;
    mSymtbl[paramDecl->name] = alloca;
  }

  if (!fty->getReturnType()->isVoidTy()) {
    auto retval = entryIrb.CreateAlloca(fty->getReturnType(), nullptr, "retval");
    entryIrb.CreateStore(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(fty->getReturnType()), retval);
    mSymtbl["retval"] = retval;
  }

  mCurFunc = func;
  self(obj->body);
  auto& exitIrb = *mCurIrb;

  if (fty->getReturnType()->isVoidTy())
    exitIrb.CreateRetVoid();
  else
    exitIrb.CreateUnreachable();
}

reasoning_content:
Let me look at the issue. The problem is that `ReturnStmt` handler creates a `return_exit` block even when there's a terminator already. The return statement creates a `ret` instruction, then creates a new `return_exit` block. But when there are multiple return statements (like in an if/else), this causes orphaned blocks.

The current code:
```cpp
void EmitIR::operator()(ReturnStmt* obj)
{
  auto& irb = *mCurIrb;
  if (!obj->expr) {
    irb.CreateRetVoid();
  } else {
    auto retVal = self(obj->expr);
    irb.CreateRet(retVal);
  }
  auto exitBb = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(mCtx, "return_exit", mCurFunc);
  irb.SetInsertPoint(exitBb);
}
```

This creates the ret, then creates a new unreachable block after it. The issue is that for the answer IR, the pattern is different - it uses retval + br pattern:
```llvm
store i32 1, ptr %retval, align 4
br label %return
...
return:
  %1 = load i32, ptr %retval, align 4
  ret i32 %1
```

This is quite different from what we're doing. Let me rethink the approach. The clang-generated IR uses:
- A `retval` alloca 
- All returns store to retval then branch to a `return` label
- The `return` label loads from retval and returns

Our current approach just emits `ret` directly and creates a dead block after. This needs to be restructured to use the retval pattern. But this is a significant refactoring. Let me check whether this is actually what we should do...

Let me check the answer IR more carefully to understand the pattern.

